# Python
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo

# HuggingFace / sentence-transformers caches that may land in CWD when a
# tool runs with HF_HOME unset or empty (e.g. an install-sandbox shell
# that forgets to pin the cache path). The model is ~90 MB — keep it
# out of the repo regardless.
hub/
xet/

# macOS / editors
.DS_Store
*.swp
*~

# Ephemeral fairy worktrees — Claude Code's Agent tool with
# isolation:"worktree" creates one git worktree per sub-agent dispatch
# under .claude/worktrees/agent-<id>/. They're cleaned up after each fairy
# returns; ignoring them keeps the repo clean if a cleanup is ever missed
# or while a fairy is mid-run. Ignore ONLY the worktrees subdir —
# .claude/agents/*.md are tracked and must stay so.
.claude/worktrees/

# Sleep-cycle cohort scratch space — dream-cohort-YYYY-MM-DD dirs written
# by cohort_dispatch.py prepare live here. Project-internal so fairy
# Read/Write access works without per-folder settings.json allowlist config.
# Gitignored because these are ephemeral sleep-cycle artifacts.
.claude/agent-scratch/

# Playwright MCP scratch dir (browser-driven verification sessions).
.playwright-mcp/

# Local working-notes desk — per Lei 2026-05-14: active-work/ is for
# in-flight notes (audits, plans, drafts) that don't need versioning.
# Tracked-by-default policy proved noisy: PRs of pure-doc working notes
# add review overhead with no code-change value, and the docs go stale
# after the work ships. Better as a local desk; if a note becomes
# canonical, promote it to docs/ or skills/ explicitly.
active-work/

# Plugin build output — assembled by tools/build-plugin.sh from canonical
# sources. Not checked in (it's a build artifact, not source). Rebuild with:
#   bash tools/build-plugin.sh
/build/
/.claude/scheduled_tasks.lock

# Personal-name roster for scan-leaks.py — gitignored by design.
# A committed roster defeats the purpose of the scanner (the names appear
# in the very file that's supposed to prevent them leaking). Authors
# populate this locally; see .scan-leaks-local.json.example for the shape.
.scan-leaks-local.json
.venv-dev/
